data.name: tabDim.ToolTip
data.value:
If any effect exceed this threshhold, then ALL of the effect on the channel will be dimmed (scaled) by the specified percentage.
The Dim, Trim, and On-Off rules are mutually exclusive and no channel may be in more than one group. The minimum time rule may be combined with Dim, Trim or On-Off.

data.name: tabTrim.ToolTip
data.value:
If any effect exceed this threshhold, those effects will be trimmed (truncated) to the specified percentage.
The Dim, Trim, and On-Off rules are mutually exclusive and no channel may be in more than one group. The minimum time rule may be combined with Dim, Trim or On-Off.

data.name: tabOnOff.ToolTip
data.value:
All effects on these channels must be either on or off. No dimming allowed! Any effect below 50% will be turned off, above 50% will be turned on. Twinkle and Shimmer effects will be changed to simple 100% on.
This rule is sometimes combined with the minimum time rule (but doesn't have to be).
The Dim, Trim, and On-Off rules are mutually exclusive and no channel may be in more than one group. The minimum time rule may be combined with Dim, Trim or On-Off.

data.name: tabMinTime.ToolTip
data.value:
These channels must stay on or off for at least the specified number of seconds. (Suggested for strobes, anything motorized, and devices with transformers) Effects will be extended as necessary to ensure they stay on or off long enough.
The minimum time rule is typically combined with the On-Off rule but may be combined with the Dim or Trim rule instead (or none of them).
